![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1000/1*DDBktCTx1jDjkhPVVjdMmA.png)

To give you some context, this function, expandArgs, is called in another function named getArgs. All these are part of [cli.js file in Nue.js source code.](https://github.com/nuejs/nue/blob/master/packages/nuekit/src/cli.js#L25) Nue.js a web framework.

### expandArgs

```plaintext
// [-npe] --> [-n, -p, -e]
export function expandArgs(args) {
  const arr = []
  args.forEach(arg => {
    if (arg[0] == '-' && arg[1] != '-' && arg[2]) {
      arg.slice(1).split('').forEach(el => arr.push('-' + el))
    } else {
      arr.push(arg)
    }
  })
  return arr
}
```

You will find this above code in [packages/nuekit/src/cli.js](https://github.com/nuejs/nue/blob/master/packages/nuekit/src/cli.js#L25). The comment just above this function explains what this function does.

